 ## [Unreleased]
 
+### Added
+
+- **Currency-aware money display formatter** (`formatMoney`, ADR 0004). The
+  display-side pair to the rounding (ADR 0002) and add/subtract (ADR 0003) money
+  primitives: `formatMoney(value, currency, locale?)` turns a stored ledger value
+  into a locale-correct currency string (`$1,234.50`, `1.234,56 €`, `¥1,235`).
+  It normalizes through `roundMoney` first, so what the user sees can never drift
+  from what the ledger stores — `formatMoney(addMoney(0.1, 0.2, "USD"), "USD")`
+  is exactly `"$0.30"`, never `"$0.30000000000000004"`. Symbol, grouping, and
+  minor-unit precision are delegated to `Intl.NumberFormat` (JPY→0 decimals,
+  USD→2, BHD→3); `locale` defaults to `"en-US"`. Fail-loud: a non-finite or
+  mixed-currency value throws `MoneyArithmeticError`, a blank/unknown currency
+  throws `RangeError`. Pure and side-effect-free. Backed by 8 new unit tests
+  (full suite 42/42 green).
+
